Task 1: Web 2.0

a) Name three characteristics of the Web 2.0
- users not only consume Web Applications but they also provide content
- users create, edit, and distribute content
- internet is no longer to get information


b) Is the Web 2.0 still the state of the art? Discuss the question by writing down three
arguments for and against the statement.

Pro:
- social sites e.g facebook are quite common
- were not only getting information on the internet, but also buy things and network

Against:
- today we have a "thinking web", we not only type something in our search engine any more,
the search engine interprets our search referring to our place and social background

- computer can understand now a days human created content
- computers can set information in relation to each other
